.RH MOD.RECIPES-SOURCE GINGER-COOKIES D "20 Oct 86" 1987
.RZ "GINGER COOKIES" "Ginger cookies"
(Originally from \fIThe Settlement Cook Book.\fR)
.PP
These have a lot of zest.
.IH "4 dozen cookies"
.IG "\(34 cup" "butter" "175 g"
.IG "1 cup" "sugar" "200 g"
.IG "\(14 cup" "dark molasses" "60 ml"
.IG "1" "egg"
.IG "2 cups" "flour" "200 g"
.IG "2 tsp" "baking soda" "10 ml"
.IG "1 tsp" "ginger" "5 ml"
.IG "1 tsp" "cinnamon" "5 ml"
.IG "1 tsp" "ground cloves" "5 ml"
.PH
.SK 1
Cream the butter and sugar togather.
.SK 2
Add the egg (beaten) and the molasses.
.SK 3
Sift the rest of the dry ingredients together and add to the mixture.
.SK 4
Form into
.AB "1-inch" "3-cm"
balls and roll in granulated sugar.
.SK 5
Place
.AB "2 inches" "6 cm"
apart on a greased cookie sheet and bake at
.TE 350 175
for 10 to 12 minutes.
.SH RATING
.I Difficulty:
easy.
.I Time:
10 minutes preparation, 10 minutes cooking.
.I Precision:
measure the ingredients.
.WR
Evelyn C. Leeper
